.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-dashboard - Launch the interactive TUI dashboard


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel dashboard [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Launches a full-screen interactive dashboard showing real-time node status,
system resources, GPU utilization, network peers, and managed services.

.PP
The dashboard auto-refreshes every 5 seconds. Press 'r' to refresh manually,
\&'a' to toggle auto-refresh, or 'q' to quit.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for dashboard


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Launch the dashboard
  citadel dashboard

  # Short alias
  citadel dash
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
